{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846843655,"sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","part":{"id":"prt_d78b84f3d0019WppeYQ1ufespZ","messageID":"msg_d78b8422d001X2tm6vWgLtcpTW","sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d9c4f48841204bbfaebf3e13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: \n12: ## Atomic Tasks\n13: \n14: ### Phase 1: GC Policy & Configuration\n15: \n16: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `GCConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go`\n17:   - Fields: `Enabled` (bool), `Interval` (time.Duration), `IdleTimeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleCount` (int), `DryRun` (bool)\n18:   - Document each field with comments\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultGCConfig()` function\n21:   - Returns default configuration: Enabled=true, Interval=5m, IdleTimeout=30m, MaxIdleCount=100, DryRun=false\n22: \n23: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxState` enum/consts in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/state.go`\n24:   - States: `StateActive`, `StateIdle`, `StateOrphaned`, `StateExpired`\n25:   - Document state transition rules\n26: \n27: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `GCCandidate` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate.go`\n28:   - Fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `State`, `LastActivity` (time.Time), `CreatedAt` (time.Time), `OwnerRef` (string)\n29:   - Methods: `IsExpired()`, `IsIdle()`\n30: \n31: ### Phase 2: GC Core Logic\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `GarbageCollector` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go`\n34:   - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `workloadManager`, `ctx`, `cancel`, `ticker`, `metrics`\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewGarbageCollector()` constructor\n37:   - Takes config, clientset, workloadManager\n38:   - Returns initialized *GarbageCollector\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Start()` method\n41:   - Creates context\n42:   - Starts ticker with configured interval\n43:   - Runs initial GC scan\n44:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Stop()` method\n47:   - Cancels context\n48:   - Stops ticker\n49:   - Logs shutdown\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `runGC()` method\n52:   - Scans all sandboxes\n53:   - Evaluates each against GC policy\n54:   - Collects candidates for cleanup\n55:   - Executes cleanup\n56:   - Records metrics\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `scanSandboxes()` method\n59:   - Lists all AgentRuntime sandboxes\n60:   - Lists all CodeInterpreter sandboxes\n61:   - Evaluates state for each\n62:   - Returns list of GCCandidate\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `evaluateState()` method\n65:   - Checks last activity timestamp\n66:   - Checks owner existence\n67:   - Determines sandbox state (Active/Idle/Orphaned/Expired)\n68: \n69: - [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `cleanup()` method\n70:   - Filters candidates by state\n71:   - Respects MaxIdleCount (keeps most recent)\n72:   - Deletes expired/orphaned sandboxes\n73:   - Deletes excess idle sandboxes\n74:   - Returns cleanup summary\n75: \n76: ### Phase 3: Activity Tracking\n77: \n78: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `LastActivityTracker` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity.go`\n79:   - Tracks last activity timestamp per sandbox\n80:   - Fields: `mu` (sync.RWMutex), `activities` (map[string]time.Time)\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `RecordActivity()` method\n83:   - Updates last activity timestamp for sandbox\n84: \n85: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `GetLastActivity()` method\n86:   - Returns last activity timestamp or zero time\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `GetIntegrations()` for activity sources\n89:   - HTTP request middleware integration point\n90:   - Session creation/deletion hooks\n91: \n92: ### Phase 4: Metrics\n93: \n94: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `GCMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go`\n95:   - Fields: `gcRuns` (Counter), `gcDuration` (Histogram), `sandboxesScanned` (Gauge), `sandboxesCleaned` (Counter), `sandboxesByState` (GaugeVec)\n96: \n97: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewGCMetrics()` constructor\n98:   - Creates Prometheus metrics\n99:   - Registers with registerer\n100: \n101: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement metric methods\n102:   - `recordRun(duration time.Duration)`\n103:   - `recordScanned(count int)`\n104:   - `recordCleaned(count int)`\n105:   - `updateStateCounts(stateCounts map[SandboxState]int)`\n106: \n107: ### Phase 5: Configuration Integration\n108: \n109: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Add GC flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n110:   - Flags: `--gc-enabled`, `--gc-interval`, `--gc-idle-timeout`, `--gc-max-idle-count`, `--gc-dry-run`\n111: \n112: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Integrate GC with main startup\n113:   - Load config\n114:   - Create GarbageCollector\n115:   - Start GC as goroutine\n116:   - Register shutdown hook\n117: \n118: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Document environment variables\n119:   - `GC_ENABLED`, `GC_INTERVAL`, `GC_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `GC_MAX_IDLE_COUNT`, `GC_DRY_RUN`\n120: \n121: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n122: \n123: #### Unit Tests - GC Core\n124: \n125: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc_test.go`\n126:   - Given: Configured GC\n127:   - When: Start() then Stop() called\n128:   - Then: GC runs without error, graceful shutdown\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_ExpiredSandboxes`\n131:   - Given: Sandboxes exceeding idle timeout\n132:   - When: runGC() called\n133:   - Then: Expired sandboxes deleted, metrics recorded\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_OrphanedSandboxes`\n136:   - Given: Sandboxes without valid owner\n137:   - When: runGC() called\n138:   - Then: Orphaned sandboxes deleted\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_MaxIdleCount`\n141:   - Given: More idle sandboxes than MaxIdleCount\n142:   - When: runGC() called\n143:   - Then: Oldest idle sandboxes deleted, keeps most recent\n144: \n145: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_DryRun`\n146:   - Given: DryRun=true, expired sandboxes exist\n147:   - When: runGC() called\n148:   - Then: No sandboxes deleted, metrics show what would be cleaned\n149: \n150: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Active`\n151:   - Given: Sandbox with recent activity\n152:   - When: evaluateState() called\n153:   - Then: Returns StateActive\n154: \n155: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Idle`\n156:   - Given: Sandbox with no recent activity but within timeout\n157:   - When: evaluateState() called\n158:   - Then: Returns StateIdle\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Expired`\n161:   - Given: Sandbox exceeding idle timeout\n162:   - When: evaluateState() called\n163:   - Then: Returns StateExpired\n164: \n165: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Orphaned`\n166:   - Given: Sandbox with missing owner\n167:   - When: evaluateState() called\n168:   - Then: Returns StateOrphaned\n169: \n170: #### Unit Tests - Activity Tracker\n171: \n172: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestLastActivityTracker_RecordAndGet` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity_test.go`\n173:   - Given: New tracker\n174:   - When: RecordActivity() then GetLastActivity()\n175:   - Then: Returns recorded timestamp\n176: \n177: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestLastActivityTracker_GetLastActivity_NotFound`\n178:   - Given: New tracker, no activity recorded\n179:   - When: GetLastActivity() called\n180:   - Then: Returns zero time\n181: \n182: #### Unit Tests - GC Candidate\n183: \n184: - [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestGCCandidate_IsExpired` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate_test.go`\n185:   - Given: Candidate with LastActivity exceeding timeout\n186:   - When: IsExpired() called\n187:   - Then: Returns true\n188: \n189: - [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestGCCandidate_IsIdle`\n190:   - Given: Candidate with no recent activity\n191:   - When: IsIdle() called\n192:   - Then: Returns true\n193: \n194: #### Unit Tests - Metrics\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestGCMetrics_RecordRun` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics_test.go`\n197:   - Given: Metrics registered\n198:   - When: recordRun() called\n199:   - Then: Counter and histogram updated\n200: \n201: - [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestGCMetrics_RecordCleaned`\n202:   - Given: Metrics registered\n203:   - When: recordCleaned() called\n204:   - Then: Counter incremented\n205: \n206: #### Test Infrastructure\n207: \n208: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `newTestGC()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc_test.go`\n209:   - Creates fake clientset, config, mock workloadManager\n210:   - Returns initialized GC for testing\n211: \n212: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Create test fixtures\n213:   - `buildAgentRuntime()` - creates test AgentRuntime objects\n214:   - `buildCodeInterpreter()` - creates test CodeInterpreter objects\n215:   - `buildSandboxWithActivity()` - creates sandboxes with specific activity timestamps\n216: \n217: #### Integration Tests\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TEST-050**: `TestGarbageCollector_Integration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/integration_test.go`\n220:   - Use envtest or real K8s cluster\n221:   - Create sandboxes with various states\n222:   - Run GC\n223:   - Verify correct sandboxes cleaned\n224: \n225: - [ ] **TEST-051**: `TestGarbageCollector_PeriodicRun`\n226:   - Start GC with short interval\n227:   - Verify GC runs periodically\n228:   - Verify metrics accumulated\n229: \n230: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n231: \n232: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/doc.go`\n233:   - Package overview\n234:   - GC strategy description\n235:   - Configuration options\n236: \n237: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n238: \n239: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Document GC policy decision logic in code comments\n240:   - State evaluation rules\n241:   - Cleanup priority order\n242: \n243: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md`\n244:   - Add GC section\n245:   - Document configuration options\n246:   - List environment variables\n247: \n248: ## Acceptance Criteria\n249: \n250: - [ ] GC runs periodically at configured interval\n251: - [ ] Expired sandboxes (exceeding idle timeout) are cleaned\n252: - [ ] Orphaned sandboxes (missing owner) are cleaned\n253: - [ ] MaxIdleCount limit enforced (oldest idle sandboxes removed)\n254: - [ ] DryRun mode logs without deleting\n255: - [ ] Activity tracking integrated with HTTP middleware\n256: - [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n257: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n258: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n259: - [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented\n260: - [ ] Configuration via flags and environment variables\n261: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n262: \n263: ## Dependencies\n264: \n265: - **Required**: pkg/workloadmanager base module\n266: - **Required**: Access to K8s clientset for listing/deleting sandboxes\n267: - **Related**: AR-007 (K8s Reconciler) - GC coordinates with reconciler state\n\n(End of file - total 267 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: GC Policy & Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `GCConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go`\n  - Fields: `Enabled` (bool), `Interval` (time.Duration), `IdleTimeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleCount` (int), `DryRun` (bool)\n  - Document each field with comments\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultGCConfig()` function","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775846843625,"end":1775846843653}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846843656,"sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","part":{"id":"prt_d78b8544b001m4FpMbHZaqcjiS","messageID":"msg_d78b8422d001X2tm6vWgLtcpTW","sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1234cdc12d2c4f6894939d4b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Implement sandbox garbage collection mechanism for periodic cleanup of idle/orphaned sandboxes in the pkg/workloadmanager module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Design GC strategy and policies\n15: - [ ] Implement GC core logic\n16: - [ ] Add cleanup scheduling\n17: - [ ] Add unit tests\n18: - [ ] Add integration tests\n19: \n20: ## Notes\n21: \n22: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n23: \n24: ## Source Files\n25: \n26: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement sandbox garbage collection mechanism for periodic cleanup of idle/orphaned sandboxes in the pkg/workloadmanager module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Design GC strategy and policies\n- [ ] Implement GC core logic\n- [ ] Add cleanup scheduling\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md","time":{"start":1775846843629,"end":1775846843655}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846843658,"sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","part":{"id":"prt_d78b859b5001vpofYaDJL5OG6j","messageID":"msg_d78b8422d001X2tm6vWgLtcpTW","sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_86c8a46da2134614bb5f14d4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n18:   - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n19:   - Document each method purpose\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `Request` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n22:   - Fields: `Namespace` (string), `Name` (string)\n23:   - Document usage in reconciliation loop\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `Result` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Requeue` (bool), `RequeueAfter` (time.Duration)\n27:   - Document requeue behavior and priorities\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `ReconcilerConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n30:   - Fields: `ResyncPeriod`, `MaxRetries`, `RateLimitQPS`, `RateLimitBurst`, `ConcurrentReconciles`, `EnableLeaderElection`, `LeaderElectionNamespace`, `LeaderElectionName`\n31:   - All fields documented with comments\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `DefaultReconcilerConfig()` function\n34:   - Returns default configuration per design spec\n35:   - Defaults: ResyncPeriod=10m, MaxRetries=5, RateLimitQPS=10, RateLimitBurst=20, ConcurrentReconciles=2\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define error constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n38:   - Constants: `ErrReconcileFailed`, `ErrPodCreationFailed`, `ErrPodUpdateFailed`, `ErrStatusUpdateFailed`, `ErrOwnerRefFailed`, `ErrCacheMiss`, `ErrInvalidSpec`\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ReconcileError` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n41:   - Fields: `Type` (string), `Message` (string), `Err` (error), `Retryable` (bool)\n42:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-008**: Implement `IsRetryableError()` function\n45:   - Checks `*ReconcileError.Retryable`\n46:   - Checks k8s transient errors: `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests`, `IsServerTimeout`\n47: \n48: ### Phase 2: ControllerManager Infrastructure\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ControllerManager` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n51:   - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `informerFactory`, `reconcilers`, `ctx`, `cancel`\n52:   - Informer fields: `agentRuntimeInformer`, `codeInterpreterInformer`, `podInformer`\n53:   - Lister fields: `agentRuntimeLister`, `codeInterpreterLister`, `podLister`\n54:   - Event recorder: `recorder`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewControllerManager()` constructor\n57:   - Creates versioned clientset and kubernetes clientset\n58:   - Initializes SharedInformerFactory with 10m resync\n59:   - Returns initialized *ControllerManager or error\n60: \n61: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `AddReconciler()` method\n62:   - Appends reconciler to manager's reconcilers slice\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `SetupInformers()` method\n65:   - Gets typed informers from factory\n66:   - Returns error if setup fails\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `StartInformers()` method\n69:   - Starts informer factory\n70:   - Waits for cache sync with timeout\n71:   - Verifies critical informers synced (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod)\n72:   - Gets listers from informers\n73: \n74: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `Start()` method\n75:   - Starts informers\n76:   - Waits for cache sync\n77:   - Starts all reconcilers as goroutines\n78:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n79:   - Handles graceful shutdown (workqueue drain)\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement graceful shutdown in `Start()`\n82:   - Shuts down workqueues\n83:   - Waits for workqueue.Done()\n84:   - Logs shutdown progress\n85: \n86: ### Phase 3: AgentRuntimeReconciler\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `AgentRuntimeReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go`\n89:   - Fields: `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `lister`, `podLister`, `recorder`, `workqueue`, `metrics`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewAgentRuntimeReconciler()` constructor\n92:   - Creates reconciler with rate-limiting workqueue\n93:   - Registers event handlers on AgentRuntime informer\n94:   - Registers event handlers on Pod informer (for owned pods)\n95:   - Returns initialized *AgentRuntimeReconciler\n96: \n97: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `Run()` method for AgentRuntimeReconciler\n98:   - Creates context from stopCh\n99:   - Starts reconciliation workers (ConcurrentReconciles workers)\n100:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n103:   - Fetches AgentRuntime from lister\n104:   - Handles NotFound (skip reconciliation)\n105:   - Handles deletion (calls `reconcileDeletion()`)\n106:   - Reconciles sandbox pod (calls `reconcileSandboxPod()`)\n107:   - Updates status (calls `updateStatus()`)\n108:   - Records events and metrics\n109:   - Returns Result with requeue logic\n110: \n111: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method\n112:   - Handles finalizer cleanup\n113:   - Deletes owned sandbox pod\n114:   - Removes finalizer\n115:   - Returns Result\n116: \n117: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method\n118:   - Checks if pod exists (from lister cache)\n119:   - If not found: builds and creates new pod\n120:   - If exists: checks if update needed\n121:   - If needs update: delete-and-recreate\n122:   - Returns pod or error\n123: \n124: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement event handler methods\n125:   - `enqueueObject(obj interface{})` - casts to AgentRuntime, enqueues Request\n126:   - `enqueueUpdate(old, new interface{})` - handles updates\n127:   - `enqueueDelete(obj interface{})` - handles deletions\n128:   - `enqueueOwnedPod(obj interface{})` - finds owner, enqueues AgentRuntime\n129:   - `enqueueOwnedPodUpdate(old, new interface{})`\n130:   - `enqueueOwnedPodDelete(obj interface{})`\n131: \n132: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterReconciler\n133: \n134: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `CodeInterpreterReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go`\n135:   - Fields: same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCodeInterpreterReconciler()` constructor\n138:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n139:   - Registers event handlers on CodeInterpreter informer\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Run()` method for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n142: \n143: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n144:   - Same reconciliation pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n145:   - Handles CodeInterpreter CRD\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method for CodeInterpreter\n148: \n149: - [ ] **TASK-035**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n150:   - Builds pod from CodeInterpreter spec\n151:   - Same create/update/delete pattern\n152: \n153: - [ ] **TASK-036**: Implement event handler methods for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n154: \n155: ### Phase 5: SandboxProcessor\n156: \n157: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `