tusUpdater` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater.go`\n203:   - Field: `clientset`\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `NewStatusUpdater()` constructor\n206: \n207: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus()` method\n208:   - Creates deep copy of AgentRuntime\n209:   - Sets Phase based on pod state\n210:   - Sets SandboxRef\n211:   - Builds Conditions from pod\n212:   - Updates Endpoint if pod running\n213:   - Skips update if status unchanged\n214:   - Calls UpdateStatus subresource\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus()` method\n217:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntime\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Implement `mapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase()` function\n220:   - Maps PodPhase to AgentRuntimePhase/CodeInterpreterPhase\n221:   - Handles: Pending, Running, Failed, Succeeded, Unknown\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TASK-055**: Implement `buildConditionsFromPod()` function\n224:   - Converts PodConditions to CRD Conditions\n225: \n226: - [ ] **TASK-056**: Implement `buildEndpointFromPod()` function\n227:   - Builds endpoint URL from PodIP and container port\n228: \n229: ### Phase 7: OwnerReference Management\n230: \n231: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `SetControllerReference()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference.go`\n232:   - Uses `metav1.NewControllerRef()`\n233:   - Sets owner reference on child object\n234: \n235: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `IsOwnedBy()` function\n236:   - Checks if object has owner reference with matching UID and Controller=true\n237: \n238: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `GetControllerOf()` helper\n239:   - Returns controller owner reference if exists\n240: \n241: ### Phase 8: Metrics\n242: \n243: - [ ] **TASK-070**: Implement `ReconcilerMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics.go`\n244:   - Fields: `reconcileDuration` (Histogram), `reconcileErrors` (Counter), `reconcileTotal` (Counter), `workqueueDepth` (Gauge), `workqueueLatency` (Histogram)\n2