ntation complete\n526: \n527: ## Dependencies\n528: \n529: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (client-go typed clients, informers, listers)\n530: - **Required**: CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) registered and served\n531: - **Required**: RBAC permissions for watching CRDs and managing Pods\n532: - **Required**: SharedInformerFactory operational\n533: - **Related**: AR-004 (HTTP server) - reconciler runs alongside HTTP server\n\n(End of file - total 533 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n  - Document each method purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775846843631,"end":1775846843656}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846843661,"sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","part":{"id":"prt_d78b85f54001AYpjYaiA66s7O5","messageID":"msg_d78b8422d001X2tm6vWgLtcpTW","sessionID":"ses_28747d297ffexyaGlTcDQblQ3b","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c11bf6197a974eaabd4a707c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `DeleteSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n18:   - Field: `Message` (string)\n19:   - JSON tag: `{\"message\":\"...\"}`\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `SandboxCleanupReason` type and constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n22:   - Type: `type SandboxCleanupReason string`\n23:   - Constants: `CleanupReasonManual`, `CleanupReasonIdleTimeout`, `CleanupReasonExpired`\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `CleanupAuditEntry` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n26:   - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `Namespace` (string), `Reason` (SandboxCleanupReason), `DeletedAt` (time.Time), `Success` (bool), `ErrorMessage` (string, omitempty)\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define lifecycle constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n29:   - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), `GCInterval` (15s), `GCSingleTickTimeout` (2m), `DeleteTimeout` (30s)\n30: \n31: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define label/annotation keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n32:   - Keys: `SessionIDLabelKey`, `WorkloadNameLabelKey`, `SandboxNameLabelKey`, `LastActivityAnnotationKey`, `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey`, `ManagedByLabel`\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: GarbageCollector Infrastructure\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `garbageCollector` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n37:   - Fields: `k8sClient` (*K8sClient), `storeClient` (store.Store), `interval` (time.Duration), `ctx` (context.Context), `cancel` (context.CancelFunc)\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `newGarbageCollector()` constructor\n40:   - Parameters: k8sClient, storeClient, interval\n41:   - Creates context with context.WithCancel\n42:   - Returns initialized *garbageCollector\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Start()` method for GarbageCollector\n45:   - Launches `gcLoop()` as goroutine\n46:   - Non-blocking\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Stop()` method for GarbageCollector\n49:   - Calls cancel() to signal shutdown\n50:   - Graceful termination\n51: \n52: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `gcLoop()` method\n53:   - Creates ticker with gc.interval\n54:   - Select on ctx.Done() and ticker.C\n55:   - Calls `tick()` on each tick\n56:   - Logs start/stop messages\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `tick()` method\n59:   - Creates context with GCSingleTickTimeout\n60:   - Calculates idleThreshold (now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout) and expiredThreshold (now)\n61:   - Calls ListInactiveSandboxes with limit 16\n62:   - Calls ListExpiredSandboxes with limit 16\n63:   - For each sandbox, calls `deleteSandbox()` with appropriate reason\n64: \n65: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `deleteSandbox()` method\n66:   - Creates CleanupAuditEntry\n67:   - Determines GVR based on Kind (SandboxClaim vs Sandbox)\n68:   - Creates delete context with DeleteTimeout\n69:   - Calls dynamicClient.Delete\n70:   - Treats K8s NotFound as success\n71:   - Calls DeleteSandboxBySessionID on success\n72:   - Logs warning on Store delete failure (doesn't fail request)\n73:   - Calls `recordAudit()`\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `recordAudit()` method\n76:   - Logs audit entry as info level\n77:   - Structured logging with entry fields\n78: \n79: ### Phase 3: Delete Handler\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `HandleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go`\n82:   - Extract sessionId from gin.Context.Param(\"sessionId\")\n83:   - Validate sessionId non-empty → 400 if empty\n84:   - Call store.GetSandboxBySessionID\n85:   - Handle ErrNotFound → 404 with message containing session id\n86:   - Handle other store errors → 500\n87:   - Determine GVR based on SandboxInfo.Kind\n88:   - Call dynamicClient.Delete with DeleteTimeout\n89:   - Treat K8s NotFound as success\n90:   - Call DeleteSandboxBySessionID (log warning on failure)\n91:   - Return 200 with DeleteSandboxResponse\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Register DELETE routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n94:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → HandleDeleteSandbox\n95:   - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → HandleDeleteSandbox\n96: \n97: ### Phase 4: Server Integration\n98: \n99: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Add `garbageCollector` field to `Server` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n100: \n101: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Initialize GarbageCollector in `NewServer()`\n102:   - Call `newGarbageCollector(client, store.Storage(), GCInterval)`\n103:   - Assign to server.garbageCollector\n104: \n105: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Start GarbageCollector in `Run()` method\n106:   - Call `s.garbageCollector.Start()` before HTTP server starts\n107: \n108: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Stop GarbageCollector in `Shutdown()` method\n109:   - Call `s.garbageCollector.Stop()` before HTTP shutdown\n110: \n111: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n112: \n113: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement error mapping in handler\n114:   - sessionId empty → 400 `sessionId is required`\n115:   - Store NotFound → 404 `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n116:   - Store other error → 500 `internal server error`\n117:   - K8s API error (non-NotFound) → 500 `internal server error`\n118:   - K8s NotFound → treat as success (continue to delete store record)\n119: \n120: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement rollback strategy\n121:   - K8s delete fails (non-NotFound): don't delete store record, return 500\n122:   - K8s delete succeeds but Store delete fails: log warning, don't return error\n123:   - K8s returns NotFound: continue to delete store record, return 200\n124: \n125: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n126: \n127: #### Unit Tests - Handler\n128: \n129: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_test.go`\n130:   - Given: session exists in store and K8s\n131:   - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n132:   - Then: 200, response contains \"Sandbox deleted successfully\"\n133:   - Verify: store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID called\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (TestCase-WM-004)\n136:   - Given: session not in store\n137:   - When: DELETE invoked\n138:   - Then: 404, message contains session id and \"not found\"\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_KubernetesNotFound`\n141:   - Given: session in store but not in K8s\n142:   - When: DELETE invoked\n143:   - Then: 200 (K8s NotFound treated as success), store record deleted\n144: \n145: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_SandboxClaim`\n146:   - Given: Kind=SandboxClaim in store\n147:   - When: DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId\n148:   - Then: 200, SandboxClaim deleted (not Sandbox)\n149: \n150: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_EmptySessionId`\n151:   - Given: sessionId is empty string\n152:   - When: DELETE invoked\n153:   - Then: 400, message contains \"sessionId is required\"\n154: \n155: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_StoreError`\n156:   - Given: store returns non-NotFound error\n157:   - When: DELETE invoked\n158:   - Then: 500, message \"internal server error\"\n159: \n160: #### Unit Tests - GarbageCollector\n161: \n162: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_IdleSandboxes` in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n163:   - Given: ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandbox\n164:   - When: tick() called\n165:   - Then: sandbox deleted from K8s and store\n166: \n167: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ExpiredSandboxes`\n168:   - Given: ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandbox\n169:   - When: tick() called\n170:   - Then: sandbox deleted from K8s and store\n171: \n172: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_KubernetesNotFound`\n173:   - Given: sandbox in store but not in K8s\n174:   - When: tick() called\n175:   - Then: store record still deleted, no error\n176: \n177: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop`\n178:   - Given: initialized GC\n179:   - When: Start() then Stop() called\n180:   - Then: gcLoop exits cleanly (no panic, context cancelled)\n181: \n182: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_BothLists`\n183:   - Given: both idle and expired sandboxes returned\n184:   - When: tick() called\n185:   - Then: all sandboxes processed, no duplicates if overlap\n186: \n187: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ListInactiveError`\n188:   - Given: ListInactiveSandboxes returns error\n189:   - When: tick() called\n190:   - Then: error logged, continues to ListExpiredSandboxes\n191: \n192: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ListExpiredError`\n193:   - Given: ListExpiredSandboxes returns error\n194:   - When: tick() called\n195:   - Then: error logged, doesn't crash\n196: \n197: #### Test Infrastructure\n198: \n199: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `buildUnstructuredSandbox()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n200:   - Returns *unstructured.Unstructured with apiVersion, kind, metadata\n201:   - Sets required labels\n202: \n203: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `buildUnstructuredSandboxClaim()` helper\n204:   - Similar to above but for SandboxClaim\n205: \n206: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock store interface\n207:   - Mock Store with methods: GetSandboxBySessionID, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes\n208: \n209: #### Integration Tests\n210: \n211: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_DeleteSandbox` in `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n212:   - Deploy AgentCube (Helm to Kind)\n213:   - Create sandbox via POST /v1/agent-runtime\n214:   - Verify sandbox accessible\n215:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n216:   - Verify 200 response\n217:   - Verify sandbox deleted (GET should 404)\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestE2E_GarbageCollector_IdleTimeout`\n220:   - Create sandbox\n221:   - Wait for idle timeout (15m + GCInterval)\n222:   - Verify sandbox auto-deleted by GC\n223: \n224: - [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestE2E_GarbageCollector_Expired`\n225:   - Create sandbox with short TTL (override for test)\n226:   - Wait for expiration\n227:   - Verify sandbox auto-deleted by GC\n228: \n229: #### Coverage Verification\n230: \n231: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n232:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n233:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n234:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n235: \n236: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n237: \n238: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n239:   - Example DELETE request/response for AgentRuntime\n240:   - Example DELETE request/response for CodeInterpreter\n241: \n242: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n243:   - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n244:   - Explain K8s NotFound treated as success\n245: \n246: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Document GarbageCollector behavior\n247:   - GC interval, batch size, timeout values\n248:   - Cleanup reasons (manual/idle_timeout/expired)\n249:   - Audit logging\n250: \n251: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add configuration options to README\n252:   - Environment variables for GC_INTERVAL, SANDBOX_TTL, IDLE_TIMEOUT\n253:   - Default values and recommended ranges\n254: \n255: ## Acceptance Criteria\n256: \n257: - [ ] Delete handler implemented for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n258: - [ ] GarbageCollector implemented with idle and expired cleanup\n259: - [ ] All handlers and GC routes registered\n260: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n261: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n262: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n263: - [ ] K8s NotFound treated as success (verified by tests)\n264: - [ ] Store delete failures logged as warnings (not returned to client)\n265: - [ ] GC runs every 15s with 2m tick timeout\n266: - [ ] GC batch size 16 for both idle and expired lists\n267: - [ ] Audit logging for all GC deletions\n268: - [ ] Server properly starts/stops GC lifecycle\n269: - [ ] Integration with Store (Get/Delete/List) verified\n270: - [ ] Integration with dynamic client (Delete) verified\n271: \n272: ## Dependencies\n273: \n274: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n275: - **Required**: Store interface operational (GetSandboxBySessionID, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes)\n276: - **Required**: dynamic client configured for Sandbox/SandboxClaim GVR\n277: - **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (for watcher cleanup on delete)\n\n(End of file - total 277 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `DeleteSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n  - Field: `Message` (string)\n  - JSON tag: `{\"message\":\"...\"}`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775846843633,"end":1775846843659}}}}
